Class Communities

Class overview

Constants and helpers for operating on communities.

This is the URI you will use for accessing information about communities. Every community which is accessible from SocialProvider has an entry in this table. You can search for communities using GLOBAL_ID, name etc. You can find information about both of the following:
  • Communities you are a member of or own.
  • All other communities that are registered in directories.
You might have different levels of information for the different types of communities.

Insert

Applications can insert communities that will be confirmed by SyncAdapters. While confirmation pending, GLOBAL_ID will be GLOBAL_ID_PENDING. Applications will have to provide the following parameters in when inserting:
  • GLOBAL_ID (needed temporally until we have a working sync adapter)
  • NAME
  • OWNER_ID
  • TYPE
  • DESCRIPTION (optional)
  • ACCOUNT_TYPE
When an application inserts a community, GLOBAL_ID will be set to GLOBAL_ID_PENDING by SocialProvider. This has to be changed by a SyncAdapter upon next successful synchronization. The sync adapter then has to write the correct global_id. While a community is pending it will not accept membership or sharing of services.
SyncAdapters cannot insert new communities.

Update

Applications can update:
  • NAME
  • TYPE
  • DESCRIPTION
SyncAdapters can update:
  • NAME
  • TYPE
  • DESCRIPTION

Delete

Applications can delete communities. Only communities that belong to the logged-in user and that are empty can be deleted.
SyncAdapters can only delete communities that are marked for deletion.

Query

Applications and SyncAdapters can query for communities using standard query URI or using _ID as the last part of the URI.
